OL,3,C'Concerning rise in courier fraud'
OL,4,Csees elderly victims conned out of
OL,5,Cthousands
OL,7,FThe caller will explain that they need
OL,8,Fthe victim's help in a secret
OL,9,Finvestigation that they are running
OL,10,Fand once 'trust' has been established,
OL,11,Fthey ask the victim to provide their
OL,12,FPIN and credit card details, or to
OL,13,Fattend their bank and withdraw
OL,14,Fthousands of pounds in cash.
OL,16,FThe bank cards or cash are later
OL,17,Fcollected from their home address by a
OL,18,Fcourier, who is part of the criminal
OL,19,Fgroup.
