OL,3,C'Concerning rise in courier fraud'
OL,4,Csees elderly victims conned out of
OL,5,Cthousands
OL,7,FOften, the victim will be given a
OL,8,F'password' to exchange with the
OL,9,Fcourier, to make them believe this is
OL,10,Fa legitimate and secure transaction.
OL,12,FSadly, police say, this money will
OL,13,Fthen often be lost to the fraudsters.
OL,15,FIn a recent spate of incidents,
OL,16,FBedford Road, Noreuil Road, The Spain,
OL,17,FHeath Road and Wetherdown have all
OL,18,Fbeen visited by criminals pretending
OL,19,Fto be couriers appointed by the
OL,20,F'police'.
