OL,4,Csees elderly victims conned out of
OL,5,Cthousands
OL,7,FOfficers are advising that, when
OL,8,Fanswering the phone to a stranger,
OL,9,Fpeople take a few minutes to think
OL,10,Fabout what they are being asked.
OL,12,FPolice say, if the caller asks for
OL,13,Fbank cards/details, cash, jewellery,
OL,14,Fwatches or gold to be handed over, or
OL,15,Ffor you to transfer money from your
OL,16,Fbank account and into another 'safe'
OL,17,Fbank account, then Hampshire and Isle
OL,18,Fof Wight Constabulary are 100 per cent
OL,19,Fconfident that this is a fake call
OL,20,Fwhich should be terminated immediately.
